---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Shaiva Vaishnava Shaktheya Homam | Holistic Tri-Tradition Fire Ritual | Nagayakshi Temple">

  <section class="pooja-hero">
    <div class="pooja-hero-overlay"></div>
    <div class="pooja-hero-content">
      <span class="pooja-badge">Supreme Ritual</span>
      <h1>Shaiva Vaishnava Shaktheya Homam</h1>
      <p class="pooja-tagline">A grand fire ritual uniting the three great traditions of Hinduism — Shaivism, Vaishnavism, and Shaktism — acknowledging them as different facets of a single supreme reality</p>
      <div class="pooja-quick-info">
        <div class="quick-info-item">
          <span class="info-label">Frequency</span>
          <span class="info-value">Annual / Special Occasions</span>
        </div>
        <div class="quick-info-item">
          <span class="info-label">Duration</span>
          <span class="info-value">Full Day Ritual</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-ctas">
        <a href="https://forms.gle/C3eQViaTHURBS48v7" class="btn-primary-gold" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Enquire</a>
        <a href="#details" class="btn-secondary-outline">Learn More</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="pooja-section" id="details">
    <div class="pooja-container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>What is Shaiva Vaishnava Shaktheya Homam?</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="content-grid">
        <div class="content-main">
          <p class="intro-text">
            The Shaiva Vaishnava Shaktheya Homam is a holistic fire ritual that brings together the three primary paths of Hinduism — Shaivism, Vaishnavism, and Shaktism — in a single, unified ceremony. It recognises Sadashiva (Shiva), Maha Vishnu, and Devi (Sakthi) not as separate deities but as different facets of one supreme reality. Performed for collective welfare and personal transformation, it combines three principal homams: Mahaganapathi Homam, Maha Rudra Homa, and Lalitha Parameswari Homa.
          </p>
          <h3>The Three Core Homams</h3>
          <p>
            Each homam within this combined ritual addresses a specific divine principle. Together they create an unbroken chain of sacred fire — opening with obstacle removal, moving through purification, and culminating in the invocation of cosmic maternal energy — to bring complete divine grace to the devotee.
          </p>
          <div class="variant-cards">
            <div class="variant-card">
              <h4>1. Mahaganapathi Homam</h4>
              <p>
                <strong>Purpose:</strong> Removing obstacles and invoking auspicious beginnings<br>
                <strong>Tradition:</strong> Performed at the outset of all major rituals; Lord Ganapati is propitiated first to ensure the entire ceremony proceeds without interruption or impediment
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="variant-card">
              <h4>2. Maha Rudra Homa</h4>
              <p>
                <strong>Purpose:</strong> Purification, spiritual liberation, and Shiva's transformative grace<br>
                <strong>Tradition:</strong> Shaiva path; invokes Sadashiva through Sri Rudram, Namakam-Chamakam, and Maha Mrityunjaya japa for the removal of karmic afflictions and all doshas
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="variant-card">
              <h4>3. Lalitha Parameswari Homa</h4>
              <p>
                <strong>Purpose:</strong> Invoking cosmic mother power, Sakthi's dynamic energy for manifestation<br>
                <strong>Tradition:</strong> Shakta path; worships Devi as Lalitha Tripura Sundari through Lalitha Sahasranama and Durga Saptashati for courage, victory, prosperity, and cosmic balance
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="content-sidebar">
          <div class="info-box">
            <h4>Quick Facts</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Unites Shaivism, Vaishnavism &amp; Shaktism</li>
              <li>Three homams in one ceremony</li>
              <li>Performed for collective welfare</li>
              <li>Requires experienced Vedic priests</li>
              <li>Performed on major auspicious occasions</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="info-box highlight">
            <h4>Best For</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Complete life transformation</li>
              <li>Severe planetary afflictions</li>
              <li>Major business ventures</li>
              <li>Marriage &amp; family harmony</li>
              <li>Health crises &amp; recovery</li>
              <li>Spiritual advancement</li>
              <li>Cosmic balance &amp; welfare</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="tradition-section">
    <div class="pooja-container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-label">Vedic Foundations</span>
        <h2>The Philosophy of Unified Worship</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="tradition-story">
        <div class="story-image">
          <img src="/images/Noorum%20Paalum.jpeg" alt="Shaiva Vaishnava Shaktheya Homam ritual">
        </div>
        <div class="story-content">
          <h3>Three Paths, One Supreme Reality</h3>
          <p>
            The deepest teaching behind this homam is that Shaivism, Vaishnavism, and Shaktism are not competing traditions but three roads leading to the same summit. Sadashiva represents the unchanging transcendent absolute; Maha Vishnu embodies the sustaining, preserving principle that upholds dharma; and Devi Sakthi is the living dynamic energy through which all creation moves. None is higher or lower — they are inseparable aspects of a single, ultimate reality.
          </p>
          <p>
            By performing all three homams together, the ritual dismantles the boundaries between traditions. Devotees of any sampradaya find their chosen deity honoured within the ceremony, making this one of the most inclusive and universally beneficial fire rituals in the Vedic tradition. It is performed primarily for collective welfare — the well-being of families, communities, and the world at large.
          </p>
          <div class="scripture-quote">
            <p>
              &#8220;He who sees Shiva in Vishnu, Vishnu in Shakti, and Shakti in Shiva — such a devotee alone transcends the cycle of birth and death. For the wise know that the three are but one supreme reality.&#8221;
            </p>
            <span class="quote-attribution">&#8212; Skanda Purana, Teachings on Divine Unity</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="tradition-variants">
        <h3>The Complete Ritual Structure</h3>
        <div class="variant-detail">
          <h4>Opening: Mahaganapathi Homam</h4>
          <p>
            The ceremony begins with the Mahaganapathi Homam to invoke Lord Ganapati's blessings and clear all obstacles before the principal rituals commence. The sacred fire is established with proper Vedic rites, and Navagraha puja is performed to harmonise planetary energies for all participants.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="variant-detail">
          <h4>Central Phase: Maha Rudra Homa</h4>
          <p>
            The Shaiva tradition is honoured through the Maha Rudra Homa — one of the most powerful purificatory rituals in the Vedic canon. Sri Rudram, Namakam and Chamakam are chanted continuously as sacred offerings of ghee, sesame, and medicinal herbs are made into the fire. This phase invokes Sadashiva's transformative grace for the removal of karmic bondages and all forms of dosha.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="variant-detail">
          <h4>Culmination: Lalitha Parameswari Homa</h4>
          <p>
            The ceremony reaches its height with the Lalitha Parameswari Homa, invoking Devi as Lalitha Tripura Sundari — the cosmic mother who is the source of all power and manifestation. Lalitha Sahasranama and Durga Saptashati are recited as offerings are made for prosperity, victory, courage, and cosmic balance. Final aarti honours all three divine aspects simultaneously, and prasadam is distributed for collective blessings.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="booking-cta-section" id="booking">
    <div class="booking-cta-container">
      <h2>Enquire About Shaiva Vaishnava Shaktheya Homam</h2>
      <p>
        Performed on auspicious occasions for complete divine transformation<br>
        Requires advance planning for proper ritual preparation
      </p>
      <div class="booking-cta-buttons">
        <a href="https://forms.gle/C3eQViaTHURBS48v7" class="btn-primary-gold btn-large" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Enquire Now</a>
        <a href="tel:+919946373522" class="btn-secondary-outline">Call: +91 9946373522</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
.pooja-hero {
  position: relative; min-height: 70vh; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
  background: linear-gradient(rgba(82, 14, 9, 0.75), rgba(82, 14, 9, 0.9)), url('/images/Noorum%20Paalum.jpeg') center/cover;
  padding: 8rem 2rem 4rem; text-align: center;
}
.pooja-hero-overlay { position: absolute; inset: 0; background: radial-gradient(circle at 50% 50%, rgba(212, 165, 116, 0.12) 0%, transparent 60%); }
.pooja-hero-content { max-width: 900px; position: relative; z-index: 10; }
.pooja-badge { display: inline-block; background: var(--laterite-red); color: white; padding: 0.5rem 1.5rem; border-radius: 30px; font-size: 0.9rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 2px; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
.pooja-hero h1 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 4.2rem; font-weight: 700; color: white; margin-bottom: 1rem; text-shadow: 0 2px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.5); }
.pooja-tagline { font-size: 1.35rem; color: var(--bg-alt); margin-bottom: 3rem; }
.pooja-quick-info { display: flex; gap: 2rem; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-bottom: 3rem; padding: 1.8rem 2rem; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.1); backdrop-filter: blur(10px); border-radius: 12px; border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.2); }
.quick-info-item { display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; gap: 0.4rem; }
.info-label { font-size: 0.8rem; color: #ffd285; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 1px; }
.info-value { font-size: 1.15rem; color: white; font-weight: 600; }
.hero-ctas { display: flex; gap: 1.5rem; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }
.pooja-section { padding: 5rem 2rem; background: var(--bg-base); }
.pooja-container { max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto; }
.section-header { text-align: center; margin-bottom: 3rem; }
.section-header h2 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 2.8rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--laterite-red); }
.content-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr; gap: 3rem; }
.content-main { font-size: 1.05rem; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.9; }
.intro-text { font-size: 1.15rem; color: var(--laterite-dark); line-height: 1.9; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
.content-main h3 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.9rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--laterite-red); margin: 2.5rem 0 1.2rem; }
.content-main p { margin-bottom: 1.2rem; }
.variant-cards { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.2rem; margin-top: 1.5rem; }
.variant-card { background: var(--bg-alt); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 4px solid var(--gold); }
.variant-card h4 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.3rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--laterite-red); margin-bottom: 0.8rem; }
.variant-card p { font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0; }
.content-sidebar { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 2rem; }
.info-box { background: var(--bg-alt); padding: 1.8rem; border-radius: 10px; border: 2px solid #e8c9a0; }
.info-box.highlight { background: var(--laterite-dark); border-color: var(--gold); }
.info-box h4 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.3rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--laterite-red); margin-bottom: 1rem; }
.info-box.highlight h4 { color: #ffd285; }
.info-box ul { list-style: none; padding: 0; }
.info-box li { padding: 0.5rem 0 0.5rem 1.5rem; position: relative; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.6; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.05); }
.info-box.highlight li { color: var(--bg-alt); border-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.1); }
.info-box li::before { content: '✓'; position: absolute; left: 0; color: var(--laterite-red); font-weight: 700; }
.info-box.highlight li::before { color: var(--gold); }
.tradition-section { padding: 5rem 2rem; background: var(--bg-alt); }
.section-label { display: block; font-family: 'Source Serif 4', serif; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--saffron); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 3px; margin-bottom: 0.8rem; text-align: center; }
.tradition-story { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 420px 1fr; gap: 3rem; align-items: start; margin: 3rem 0; }
.story-image img { width: 100%; border-radius: 12px; box-shadow: 0 12px 40px rgba(0,0,0,0.15); }
.story-content h3 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.9rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--laterite-red); margin-bottom: 1.2rem; }
.story-content p { font-size: 1.05rem; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.9; margin-bottom: 1.4rem; }
.scripture-quote { background: var(--bg-base); padding: 1.8rem; border-radius: 10px; border-left: 4px solid var(--laterite-red); margin-top: 1.5rem; }
.scripture-quote p { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.25rem; font-style: italic; color: var(--laterite-dark); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 0.8rem; }
.quote-attribution { font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--text-muted); }
.tradition-variants { margin-top: 4rem; }
.tradition-variants h3 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--laterite-red); margin-bottom: 2rem; text-align: center; }
.variant-detail { background: var(--bg-base); padding: 2.5rem; border-radius: 10px; margin-bottom: 1.8rem; border-left: 4px solid var(--gold); }
.variant-detail h4 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--laterite-red); margin-bottom: 1rem; }
.variant-detail p { font-size: 1.05rem; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
.booking-cta-section { padding: 5rem 2rem; background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--laterite-red) 0%, #6b1f2b 100%); text-align: center; }
.booking-cta-container { max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; }
.booking-cta-container h2 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 2.8rem; font-weight: 700; color: white; margin-bottom: 1.2rem; }
.booking-cta-container p { font-size: 1.2rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.95); margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.8; }
.booking-cta-container strong { color: #ffd285; }
.booking-cta-buttons { display: flex; gap: 1.5rem; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-top: 2rem; }
.btn-large { padding: 1.4rem 3.5rem; font-size: 1.15rem; }
@media (max-width: 1024px) { .content-grid, .tradition-story { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .pooja-hero h1 { font-size: 2.8rem; }
  .pooja-quick-info { flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem; }
  .booking-cta-container h2 { font-size: 2.2rem; }
  .booking-cta-buttons { flex-direction: column; align-items: stretch; }
}
</style>
